Notebook[{

Cell[CellGroupData[{
Cell["STPreAnalysis", "ObjectName",ExpressionUUID->"33c0ac68-f675-4a71-96b3-d192f8563d54"],

Cell[BoxData[GridBox[{
   {Cell[TextData[{
     StyleBox["STPreAnalysis", "TI"],
     " \[LineSeparator]STPreAnalysis performs an extended analysis of the \
singularity structure of an Euler integrand."
    }], "TableText",ExpressionUUID->"97609626-93ec-46ad-9e28-36523a9a2c1c"]}
  },
  GridBoxAlignment->{"Columns" -> {{Left}}},
  GridBoxItemSize->{
   "Columns" -> {{Automatic}}, "Rows" -> {{Automatic}}}]], "Usage",
 CellID->1,ExpressionUUID->"1f74c98a-61c0-4e61-bd2b-19eea28a1819"],

Cell["\<\
STPreAnalysis performs an extended analysis of the singularity structure of \
an Euler integrand. It is useful for diagnosing which divergences are and are \
not regulated by a given set of regulators. (see example below)\
\>", "Notes",ExpressionUUID->"d7d050ea-c385-4d23-a5f9-14fdd4692797"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"STPreAnalysis", "[", 
   RowBox[{
   "integrand", ",", " ", "variables", ",", " ", "coefficients", "\n", "\t", ",",
     " ", "True", "       ", 
    RowBox[{"(*", " ", 
     RowBox[{"facesQ", ",", " ", "optional"}], " ", "*)"}], "\n", "\t", ",", 
    " ", 
    RowBox[{"{", "eps", "}"}]}], "  ", "]"}], "   ", 
  RowBox[{"(*", " ", 
   RowBox[{"regulators", ",", " ", "optional"}], " ", "*)"}]}]], "Input",Expre\
ssionUUID->"7874d69a-729e-42ac-80a2-11847eb5ef8a"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Details", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"1226534a-d965-416f-971d-07d14bcec772"],

Cell["Arguments", "Subsection",ExpressionUUID->"45f14471-35dd-4dcb-89be-3271b493c23f"],

Cell["\<\
integrand, variables, and coefficients follow the same conventions as in \
STExpandIntegral below. The optional argument facesQ (default True) controls \
whether to compute the divergent faces. The optional regulators (default \
{eps}) lists the parameters used to determine which rays correspond to \
divergences.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"e9438bd4-f320-4923-adc2-66c9392be049"],

Cell["Return value", "Subsection",ExpressionUUID->"28134b8c-68ba-42ad-ac38-8f37511aee49"],

Cell["\<\
An Association with keys: \"trops\" (the value of the tropical integrand Trop\
\\,I|_{\[CurlyEpsilon]=0}(\\rho) evaluated on each ray~\\rho), \"rays\" \
(indices of the divergent rays), \"faces\" (the divergent faces of the Newton \
polytope), \"us\" (the u-variables), and \"trData\" (the full tropical data \
structure including the polytope, rays, facets, and convex hull).  A zero \
entry in \"trops\" indicates that the integrand has a logarithmic singularity \
along that ray which is not regulated by the specified regulators: the \
\[CurlyEpsilon]-dependent part of the tropical integrand vanishes on this \
ray, so \[CurlyEpsilon] alone cannot render the integral finite. Such rays \
typically signal the need of a secondary regulator (e.g., the parameter q in \
the small-x example of Sec.~) and must be handled via STcontinueRays (App.~) \
before proceeding with the tropical subtraction.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"a5e1a4be-eeb9-47d5-85dc-682b9247cc91"]
}, Open  ]],

